Third-party software incorporated or referenced by SQMesh
================================================================================

The SQMesh source tree incorporates, derives from, or interoperates with the
following third-party components.  A consolidated summary of each component's
license is available in THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TetGen 1.6 (Hang Si, Weierstrass Institute for Applied Analysis and
Stochastics, Berlin, Germany)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The tetrahedral meshing core located under src/mesh/tet/core/ is a
derivative work of TetGen 1.6.  TetGen 1.6 is distributed under the GNU
Affero General Public License v3.0.  SQMesh therefore carries forward the
AGPL-3.0 license terms for the project as a whole.  Shewchuk's robust
geometric predicates have been promoted from this directory to
src/core/predicates.cxx and are shared with the auto-CFD surface mesher;
their public-domain status is unaffected (see the next section).

Reference: https://wias-berlin.de/software/tetgen/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Shewchuk's Robust Geometric Predicates (Jonathan Richard Shewchuk,
Carnegie Mellon University)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The file src/core/predicates.cxx is Jonathan Richard Shewchuk's
public-domain implementation of arbitrary-precision floating-point
arithmetic and robust geometric predicates.  It is included verbatim and
is not covered by the AGPL-3.0 license of the surrounding project.  It is
shared between the tetrahedral mesher (src/mesh/tet/core/) and the
auto-CFD surface mesher (src/mesh/auto_cfd/) via src/core/predicates.hpp.

Reference: https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~quake/robust.html

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gmsh 4.x (Christophe Geuzaine, Jean-Francois Remacle, and contributors)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SQMesh does not incorporate Gmsh source code.  MSH file format
interoperability in src/mesh/io/ is implemented independently against the
publicly documented MSH 2/4 file format specification.  Gmsh itself is
distributed under the GNU General Public License v2.0 or later, with
exceptions (see the Gmsh upstream LICENSE for details).

Reference: https://gmsh.info/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OpenCASCADE Technology (Open CASCADE S.A.S.)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SQMesh optionally links against OpenCASCADE Technology (OCCT) through the
adapter in src/cad/occ/.  OCCT is distributed under the GNU Lesser General
Public License v2.1 with an exception for certain deliveries.  Users who
build SQMesh with OCCT support must comply with OCCT's license terms when
redistributing the resulting binaries.

Reference: https://www.opencascade.com/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
spdlog (Gabi Melman)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SQMesh uses spdlog as its logging backend, distributed under the MIT
license.  spdlog is consumed via its public headers only and is not
modified by SQMesh.

Reference: https://github.com/gabime/spdlog

